399
00:20:13,550 --> 00:20:18,430
And now, we have our
types of connections.

400
00:20:18,430 --> 00:20:23,880
So our main two are workbook
and packaged workbooks.

401
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:28,600
So a workbook or otherwise
known as the .twb is--

402
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:32,430
so basically, a workbook
holds one or more worksheets

403
00:20:32,430 --> 00:20:35,250
plus zero more
dashboards and stories.

404
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:38,640
If they are shared, the receiver
cannot modify the worksheet

405
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:41,460
and does not have access
to the data source.

406
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:46,060
They simply-- or they can
simply see the visualization.

407
00:20:46,060 --> 00:20:49,470
So basically, they can only
see what's this right here.

408
00:20:49,470 --> 00:20:50,522
They cannot see this.

409
00:20:50,522 --> 00:20:51,480
There are none of this.

410
00:20:51,480 --> 00:20:55,700
They can just see
the visualization.

411
00:20:55,700 --> 00:20:57,620
And that's where a
packaged workbook--

412
00:20:57,620 --> 00:21:00,080
a packaged workbook is
a single zip file that

413
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:05,330
contains a workbook along with
any supporting local file data

414
00:21:05,330 --> 00:21:06,680
and background images.

415
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:10,280
So this format is the best way
to package your work for sharing

416
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:13,580
with others who do not have
access to your original data

417
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:16,490
because it includes
the data source.

418
00:21:16,490 --> 00:21:20,690
So it'll include-- basically
all of this basically, what

419
00:21:20,690 --> 00:21:24,040
you see on my screen right
now, it'll include that.

420
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:28,120
And also, if you
make extracts over

421
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:32,610
here and add filters and
everything, such as that,

422
00:21:32,610 --> 00:21:34,405
it will include that as well.

423
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:42,590
And then we have
bookmarks or the .tbm,

424
00:21:42,590 --> 00:21:46,520
which bookmark contains a single
worksheet and are an easy way

425
00:21:46,520 --> 00:21:48,440
to quickly share your work.

426
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:51,830
Extracts or so the hyper
is a Tableau extract

427
00:21:51,830 --> 00:21:55,670
files have the hyper extension.

428
00:21:55,670 --> 00:21:57,860
So extract files
are a local copy

429
00:21:57,860 --> 00:22:01,640
of a subset or entire data set
that you can use to share data

430
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:04,550
with others when you need
to work offline and improve

431
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:07,360
performances.

432
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:09,780
And then as for--

433
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:14,230
and then we have the .tds,
which is a Tableau data source.

434
00:22:14,230 --> 00:22:17,410
Data source files contains
all the necessary information

435
00:22:17,410 --> 00:22:19,720
regarding a data
connection made in Tableau.

436
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:23,470
So the Tableau data
source file contains

437
00:22:23,470 --> 00:22:26,740
all the required
information on setting up

438
00:22:26,740 --> 00:22:29,410
a data connection
along with the metadata

439
00:22:29,410 --> 00:22:35,110
or other specific
modifications made by the user.

440
00:22:35,110 --> 00:22:36,670
Sweet.

